Subject: RE: [T2] harmonic balancer (curiousity question)



Smoothness is the characteristic of a flat configured engine.
The firing order is set in such a way that 2 cylinders fire about the
same time in the oppositie direction.  Thus balancing out the resultant 
forces.

It is simply due to this reason that VW aircooled engines
lived such long lives. The force on main bearing is reduce
considerably. Resulting in less than normal wear.

I commend subaru for staying with the flat configuration.
Beside saving space, the are smooth and last longer.

Syed


